#MEM id=security-test-checklist source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/quinn/skills/custom/security-test-checklist/SKILL.md savings=38%
M||tx|---
M||name|sec-tst-checklist
M||desc|qn's sec gate checklist — runs before issuing any APPROVED verdict. Covers auth bypass, cross-vt isolation, rate limiting, client bundle key scan, XSS, RLS spot-check, and CORS verification. Any fl = blk.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||tx|---
M|Purp|tx|A feature that passes functional QA but has a sec hole is not ready to ship. qn is the last gate before dv merges — which means qn is also the last check that catches sec failures before they reach production. This checklist runs before every APPROVED verdict, no exceptions.
M|Purp|tx|---
M|The |tx|Run all items. Check "N/A" only if the item genuinely doesn't apply to this feature (e.g., no auth rt = auth tests N/A). Never skip w/o stating why.
M|The |tx|---
M|Auth|- [ |`401`. Actual: ___
M|Auth|- [ |`401` w/ clear message. Actual: ___
M|Auth|- [ |`401`. Actual: ___
M|Auth|it|[ ] **Auth fl rp** — Confirm the 401 body contains only a generic message. No stack trace, no rt name, no DB sc info.
M|Auth|tx|---
M|Cros|- [ |`403` or data scoped to correct vt only.
M|Cros|- [ |data remains scoped to the authenticated vt, not the tampered cookie value.
M|Cros|tx|---
M|Rate|- [ |`429` status w/ `Retry-After` header.
M|Rate|it|[ ] **Rate limit rp body** — Confirm the 429 body contains a us-safe message only. No internal rt structure exposed.
M|Rate|it|[ ] **Retry-After header present** — Confirm `Retry-After` header is included in the 429 rp.
M|Rate|tx|---
M|Clie|- [ |zero results.
M|Clie|tx|```bash
M|Clie|tx|grep -r "ANTHROPIC\\|APIFY\\|SERVICE_ROLE" .nx/static/ 2>/dv/null
M|Clie|tx|```
M|Clie|it|[ ] **NEXT_PUBLIC_ audit** — rv all `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` vars in `.env.local`. Confirm none contain secrets, ap keys, or credentials.
M|Clie|tx|---
M|XSS |- [ |script does not execute in the browser; cn is rendered as text or rejected.
M|XSS |- [ |no alert, cn rendered safely.
M|XSS |- [ |safe er rp, no crash, no DB er exposed to client.
M|XSS |tx|---
M|RLS |- [ |blk by RLS policy, zero rows returned.
M|RLS |- [ |zero rows returned (RLS scoping enforced).
M|RLS |tx|---
M|CORS|- [ |no `*` on authenticated endpoints; origin scoped to yv's domain.
M|CORS|tx|---
M|Erro|it|[ ] **Load `skills/custom/er-log-audit/SKILL.md`** and run its checklist against this feature's ap rt.
M|Erro|tx|---
M|Verd|tx|If ANY item fails (not N/A) → **blk**. Document exactly which tst failed, what was expected, and what was returned.
M|Verd|tx|```
M|Verd|Secu|PASSED / FAILED
M|Verd|Fail|
M|Verd|- [t|expected [X], got [Y]
M|Verd|Fix |[specific change needed in which file]
M|Verd|tx|```
M|Verd|tx|Three or more sec failures on the same feature → flag to dv as a pattern issue, not just a bug list.